## Language-specific rules
<!-- AI: Add rules specific to this project's primary language and framework. Remove sections that don't apply. -->

### General (all languages)
- No commented-out code in committed files — delete it or open an issue.
- No debug print/log statements in committed code — use the project logger.
- Functions do one thing. If a function needs a comment to explain what it does, split it.

### <!-- AI: e.g. TypeScript -->
- <!-- AI: e.g. No implicit `any`. Every function parameter and return type must be typed. -->
- <!-- AI: e.g. Use `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions and aliases. -->

### API / backend
- Validate all input at the route boundary before it reaches the service layer.
- Never return stack traces to the client. Log them server-side with context.
- Every service function that can fail must return a typed error, not throw.

### Database
- All queries go through the DB layer (see 12-FOLDER-STRUCTURE.md).
- No raw string interpolation in queries. Use parameterized queries only.

## Git conventions
| Thing | Convention | Example |
|-------|------------|---------|
| Commit messages | Conventional Commits | `feat: add invoice export`, `fix: resolve login loop` |
| Branch names | `type/short-description` | `feat/invoice-export`, `fix/login-loop` |
| PR titles | Same as commit format | `feat: add invoice export` |
| Protected branches | `main`, `develop` | No force-push. No direct commits. PR required. |
